when I started this video.

108
00:03:55,030 --> 00:03:59,420
This is a nice general question.
It's a very broad question.

109
00:03:59,420 --> 00:04:02,070
When you say to someone, "So,
how are things with you?"

110
00:04:02,070 --> 00:04:04,220
they can answer by talking about work,

111
00:04:04,220 --> 00:04:05,890
they can talk about their family,

112
00:04:05,890 --> 00:04:08,360
they can talk about a
new car that they bought.

113
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:11,570
It's a really good way to
start an English conversation

114
00:04:11,570 --> 00:04:14,320
because it allows the
person you are talking to

115
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:16,067
to answer in a variety of ways.

116
00:04:16,067 --> 00:04:19,870
"So, how are things with
you?" Or, "So how are things?"

117
00:04:19,870 --> 00:04:22,630
Often when talking to
a friend or a relative,

118
00:04:22,630 --> 00:04:24,080
there are things about their life

119
00:04:24,080 --> 00:04:25,490
that you already know about,

120
00:04:25,490 --> 00:04:27,640
but you want to inquire about them,

121
00:04:27,640 --> 00:04:29,320
you wanna ask questions about them.

122
00:04:29,320 --> 00:04:33,050
And we often do this by
combining the word how with is

123
00:04:33,050 --> 00:04:35,100
to make the contraction how's.

124
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:37,530
We ask questions like
this. "How's the family?

125
00:04:37,530 --> 00:04:40,070
How's the new car? How's work?"

126
00:04:40,070 --> 00:04:42,750
These are all questions where
you kind of need to know

127
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:44,650
a little bit about the person's life.

128
00:04:44,650 --> 00:04:46,460
And you can ask these questions

129
00:04:46,460 --> 00:04:48,720
and then they can kind
of give you an update.

130
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:51,640
I just used a question like
this this past weekend.

131
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:55,060
My brother-in-law, I knew
he had bought a new truck,

132
00:04:55,060 --> 00:04:57,700
