139
00:05:12,710 --> 00:05:14,950
to ask questions about the past.

140
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:17,940
You could ask questions like
this. "How was your trip?

141
00:05:17,940 --> 00:05:20,810
How was your drive? How was your weekend?

142
00:05:20,810 --> 00:05:22,450
How was your day off?"

143
00:05:22,450 --> 00:05:26,310
So we use again, the
question word how with was

144
00:05:26,310 --> 00:05:27,640
in order to ask questions

145
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:29,977
about things we know already happened.

146
00:05:29,977 --> 00:05:31,780
"How was your trip?"

147
00:05:31,780 --> 00:05:33,760
Life is full of changes.

148
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:36,600
Maybe someone has retired,
maybe they got married,

149
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:39,420
maybe they had a baby,
maybe they started a new job

150
00:05:39,420 --> 00:05:41,220
or went to university.

151
00:05:41,220 --> 00:05:43,510
And there's a fun way of asking a question

152
00:05:43,510 --> 00:05:44,860
about things like that.

153
00:05:44,860 --> 00:05:48,330
You add the phrase treating
you to the end of the question.

154
00:05:48,330 --> 00:05:50,167
So you can ask questions like this.

155
00:05:50,167 --> 00:05:52,960
"How's fatherhood treating you?
How's marriage treating you?

156
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:54,530
How's that new job treating you?

157
00:05:54,530 --> 00:05:56,410
How's retirement treating you?"

158
00:05:56,410 --> 00:05:58,610
It's just a fun way to ask someone

159
00:05:58,610 --> 00:06:00,850
about the change that's
happened in their life,

160
00:06:00,850 --> 00:06:04,080
and it gives them an
opportunity to kind of explain

161
00:06:04,080 --> 00:06:06,220
how that change has made
their life different.

162
00:06:06,220 --> 00:06:08,600
So you can ask questions just like that.

163
